 Minister of Science and Technology, Dr. Ogbonnaya Onu made the appeal when he commissioned an upgraded chemical laboratory donated by PZ Cussons at Tafawa Balewa University, Bauchi, over the weekend.  He made the appeal when he commissioned an upgraded chemical laboratory donated by PZ Cussons at Tafawa Balewa University, Bauchi, at the weekend. The minister lauded the firm for upgrading the chemical laboratory, which would address issues of transportation of research samples and others. According to the minister, Nigerians could be lifted out of poverty by nurturing business startups which would later grow in size and employ a lot of people. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .